    <oval-def:description>Harry Sintonen discovered that wget, a network utility to retrieve files from the web,
		does not properly handle '\r\n' from continuation lines while parsing the Set-Cookie HTTP header.
		A malicious web server could use this flaw to inject arbitrary cookies to the cookie jar file,
		adding new or replacing existing cookie values.</oval-def:description>
